HEADWORD: Subspecies
<hw>Sub*spe"cies</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A group somewhat
lessdistinct than speciesusually are, but based on characters more
important than those which characterize ordinary varieties; often, a
geographical variety or race.</def>⟦br⟧
